11/07/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Parliament's commission on defence and security approved the draft law on military service amnesty Thursday (10 July).
According to Justice Minister Ismail Dardhishta, the bill waives criminal charges against more than 12,300 people who failed to join the army in the past ten years.
Some lawmakers still want to levy fines or force public service work on those in question.
In other news Thursday, Martti Ahtisaari, the chairman of the International Crisis Group, told the <I>Utrinski Vesnik</I> that Macedonia has a real chance for smooth and peaceful development and prosperity.
He added that the security situation has improved considerably.
(Utrinksi Vesnik - 11/07/03;
MIA, A1 TV - 10/07/03)
